January 22, 2026
HOUSE BILL No. 1119
_____
DIGEST OF HB 1119 (Updated January 21, 2026 1:18 pm - DI 106)
Citations Affected: IC 35-38.
Synopsis: Execution methods. Authorizes the death penalty to be
carried out by firing squad or nitrogen hypoxia, in addition to lethal
injection. Removes the requirement that an execution be carried out:
(1) at the Indiana state prison; and (2) before sunrise. Exempts certain
persons from being required to participate in an execution. Makes
conforming amendments and technical corrections.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Lucas, Prescott, Bartels, Ireland
January 5, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Courts and Criminal Code.
January 22, 2026, amended, reported — Do Pass.
