1 SECTION 2. IC 35-38-6-1, AS AMENDED BY P.L.56-2023,
2 SECTION 322, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS
3 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 1. (a) Except as provided in
4 section 1.5 of this chapter, the punishment of death shall be inflicted
5 carried out by intravenous injection of a lethal substance or substances
6 into the convicted person:
7 (1) in a quantity sufficient to cause the death of the convicted
8 person; and
9 (2) until the convicted person is dead.
10 (b) The death penalty shall be inflicted carried out before the hour
11 of sunrise on a date fixed by the sentencing court. However, the
12 execution must not occur until at least one hundred (100) days after the
13 conviction.
14 (c) The warden of the appropriate state prison, or persons
15 designated by the warden, shall designate the person who is to serve as
16 the executioner.
17 (d) The department of correction may adopt rules under IC 4-22-2
18 necessary to implement subsection (a).
19 (e) The department of correction may make and enter into a contract
20 with an outsourcing facility, a wholesale drug distributor (as defined in
21 IC 25-26-14-12), a pharmacy (as defined in IC 25-26-13-2), or a
22 pharmacist (as defined in IC 25-26-13-2) for the issuance or
23 compounding of a lethal substance necessary to carry out an execution
24 by lethal injection. A lethal substance provided to the department of
25 correction under this subsection may be used only for the purpose of
26 carrying out an execution by lethal injection. The issuance or
27 compounding of a lethal substance under this subsection:
28 (1) does not constitute the practice of pharmacy (as defined in
29 IC 25-26-13-2);
30 (2) is not subject to the jurisdiction of the Indiana board of
31 pharmacy, the medical licensing board of Indiana, the Indiana
32 department of health, or the Indiana professional licensing
33 agency; and
34 (3) is exempt from the provisions of IC 25.
35 A pharmacist, a pharmacy, a wholesale drug distributor, or an
36 outsourcing facility that provides a lethal substance to the department
37 of correction under this subsection shall label the lethal substance with
38 the name of the lethal substance, its dosage, a projected expiration date,
39 and a statement that the lethal substance shall be used only by the
40 department of correction for the purpose of carrying out an execution
41 by lethal injection.
42 (f) The following are confidential, are not subject to discovery, and
