19 SECTION 3. IC 35-38-6-1.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
20 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
21 1, 2026]: Sec. 1.5. (a) The department of correction may carry out
22 an execution by:
23 (1) lethal injection;
24 (2) firing squad; or
25 (3) nitrogen hypoxia;
26 as determined by the commissioner of the department of
27 correction.
28 (b) The department of correction shall establish a facility and a
29 protocol for carrying out an execution by firing squad.
30 (c) The department of correction shall establish a facility and a
31 protocol for carrying out an execution by nitrogen hypoxia.
32 (d) An execution shall be carried out within the time frame
33 described in section 1(b) of this chapter.
34 (e) An execution by firing squad shall be carried out by a firing
35 squad consisting of three (3) individuals who are selected by the
36 warden of the prison where the execution will be carried out. Each
37 individual shall fire a weapon containing live ammunition. No
38 blanks may be used.
39 (f) The department of correction may adopt rules under
40 IC 4-22-2 necessary to implement this chapter.
41 (g) The following are confidential, are not subject to discovery,
42 and may not be introduced as evidence in any civil or criminal
